keyFacts: The analysis is focused on cross-referencing CBP records with personal flight logs from 'Rodgers' to establish detailed travel timelines for Ghislaine Maxwell and Jeffrey Epstein.
Multiple trips by Maxwell to London in 1993 and 1994 are highlighted, with the analysis noting the age of an unnamed minor (redacted) at the time of each trip.
Flight logs show Epstein and Maxwell traveling together frequently in late 1994, including a flight with two other unnamed individuals on September 22, 1994.
The earliest CBP record for an unnamed minor traveling to the US is identified as November 1, 1997.
The document is an internal defense team email, indicating active review of travel evidence in preparation for legal proceedings.
